metadata.name: Ballet & Daisies
metadata.description:
You told me to go make my own world
Put together a puzzle no one can fight
And I found myself where the fairies sing
Everything is alright 'cause I found my dream 
The whole world is still a mystery 
But I want to explore it with you
I'll just try and catch the light surrounding me and you
We'll undress our intentions with blinding kisses and hugs
Fuzzy slippers and sweets
Photos, web3 and tweets
Taking a journey by moonlight and morning dew
We got so much to offer
But we are more than what our eye seems to be
A coloring of thoughts and dreams
Eyes on you and me

We will continue to create and be
